{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":371438,"duration_api_ms":447863,"num_turns":27,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"e412034c-eb05-470d-a959-7275687bb04a","total_cost_usd":1.4486963499999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":17,"cache_creation_input_tokens":67012,"cache_read_input_tokens":842590,"output_tokens":15810,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":67012,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":17,"outputTokens":15810,"cacheReadInputTokens":842590,"cacheCreationInputTokens":67012,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.235455,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":253,"outputTokens":11376,"cacheReadInputTokens":651771,"cacheCreationInputTokens":72745,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.21324135000000005,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"BUG: Cancellation during retry backoff reports wrong failure class in run_failed journal event. In engine.rs:4642-4655, when cancellation is detected during the backoff sleep, `fail_run_result(&error, ...)` is called with the original backend error (e.g. TransportFailure). This causes `failure_label()` to return \"transport_failure\" instead of \"cancellation\". The pre-existing test `cancellation_between_retry_attempts_does_not_start_next_attempt` (workflow_engine_test.rs:3870) asserts `run_failed.details[\"failure_class\"] == \"cancellation\"` and will fail.\n\nThe sequence: (1) first attempt returns TransportFailure, (2) `will_retry` computed as true (token not cancelled yet), (3) CancelBetweenRetryAttemptsLogWriter triggers cancellation during stage_failed log write, (4) backoff select! detects cancellation, (5) fail_run_result called with original TransportFailure error → writes \"transport_failure\" not \"cancellation\".\n\nIn the old code (without the select!/cancellation check), the retry loop continued to the next attempt, where the stub adapter detected cancellation and returned InvocationCancelled, correctly producing \"cancellation\".\n\nFix: When cancellation is detected during backoff (engine.rs:4642), construct an AppError::InvocationCancelled and pass that to fail_run_result instead of the original `&error`.","rationale":"This is a correctness bug that breaks an existing test. The cancellation-during-backoff optimization changes observable behavior: the run_failed journal event records the wrong failure class. Beyond the test failure, this affects operational observability — operators inspecting failed runs would see \"transport_failure\" when the actual cause was cancellation."}],"summary":"Reviewed all 5 changed files (retry_policy.rs, engine.rs, error.rs, process_backend.rs, tests). The retry limit increases, BinaryNotFound variant addition, exponential backoff, exit code 127 classification, artifact preservation on timeout, and start_paused test annotations are all correctly implemented. Found one critical bug: the new cancellation-during-backoff path in engine.rs:4642-4655 passes the original backend error (TransportFailure) to fail_run_result instead of a Cancellation error, which breaks the existing test `cancellation_between_retry_attempts_does_not_start_next_attempt` and would misreport failure cause in the journal."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"8bf2e5d2-82c7-4707-87df-7d4eb1ca1973"}
